lots.title_primary_txt: TWO CERAMIC VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS
lots.description_txt:
Comprising: an Imari vase decorated with a continuous frieze of a blossoming cherry tree and a pair of cranes, with an eight-character mark to the underside and a famille rosevase with cream craquelure-ground decoration with various figures including a warrior, courtiers, and scholars and raised on a mahogany base; each fitted for electricity and with cream shades 
Imari vase: 23 in. (58.5 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 13 in. (33 cm.) diameter 
Cream-ground vase: 22¹⁄₂ in. (57 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 9¹⁄₄ in. (25 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: TWO CERAMIC VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS

lots.title_primary_txt: A FRENCH 'JAPONISME' PATINATED-BRONZE FIGURAL TABLE CLOCK
lots.title_secondary_txt: THE MOVEMENT BY JAPY FRERES, RETAILED BY MANOAH RHODES & SON, THIRD QUARTER 19TH CENTURY
lots.description_txt:
Modelled as a gong with hammered surface applied with wisteria and insects and centred by a circular dial with Arabic numerals and signed 'MANOAH RHODES & SONS/ PARIS', the twin barrel movement with strike on bell, held aloft by a crouching robed figure on a square base with pierced apron above four scroll feet 
12¹⁄₂ in. (31.5 cm.) high; 7 in. (17.5 cm.) wide

image.image_alt_text: A FRENCH 'JAPONISME' PATINATED-BRONZE FIGURAL TABLE CLOCK

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF JAPANESE IMARI PORCELAIN VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS
lots.description_txt:
Each vase profusely decorated with scrolling red and gilt floral decoration, the top border with cartouches depicting alternating phoenix and dragons, the body with panels depicting figures standing in front of cherry blossom trees, the underside with six character mark, with pleated cream shades, fitted for electricity 
18¹⁄₂ in. (47 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 12 in. (30.5 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF JAPANESE IMARI PORCELAIN VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS

lots.title_primary_txt: TWO JAPANESE GOLD AND BLACK LACQUER BOXES
lots.description_txt:
The larger box decorated with takamaki-e and hiramaki-edepicting blooming lotus emerging from a rocky outcrop to the top, the reverse of the cover with a landscape depicting a house by a river and enclosing a removeable tray further decorated with lotus, the sides decorated with small plants and butterflies; the smaller box decorated with hiramaki-eoverall with ferns and with two small floral handles tied with a tasseled cord, the interior lined in green and gold fabric with a metal rim 
The larger: 6¹⁄₄ in. (17.5 cm.) high; 15¹⁄₂ in. (39.5 cm.) wide; 12 in. (30.5 cm.) deep 
The smaller: 6 in. (15.5 cm.) high; 11 in. (28 cm.) wide; 10 in. (25.5 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: TWO JAPANESE GOLD AND BLACK LACQUER BOXES

lots.title_primary_txt: A GROUP OF THREE CHINESE VASES, TWO MOUNTED AS LAMPS
lots.description_txt:
Comprising: a crackle-glaze baluster vase glazed in bands of white, celadon, and ochre with French gilt and patinated-bronze base mount, a bottle form vase with wood base and fitted as a lamp with cream shade, and copper-red decorated bottle vase fading from crackled grey-green glaze with gilt-metal mounts and fitted as a lamp with cream shade 
The vase: 20 in. (51 cm.) high; 9¹⁄₄ in. (24.5 cm.) diameter 
The green lamp: 15¹⁄₄ in. (38.5 cm.) high, excluding diameter; 9¹⁄₄ in. (24.5 cm.) diameter 
The red and green lamp: 16¹⁄₄ in. (42.5 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 9 in. (23 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A GROUP OF THREE CHINESE VASES, TWO MOUNTED AS LAMPS

lots.title_primary_txt: A COLD-PAINTED METAL TORCHERE MODELLED AS A CRANE
lots.description_txt:
The patinated crane entwined amongst polychrome-decorated lotus leaves and a central stem issuing a blooming flower centred by a bobeche, on a large leaf base raised on branch feet, not fitted for electricity 
61¹⁄₄ in. (155.5 cm.) high; 19 in. (48 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A COLD-PAINTED METAL TORCHERE MODELLED AS A CRANE

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF CHINESE HONGMU HORSESHOE-BACK CHAIRS
lots.description_txt:
Each with a vertical slat carved with shou roundel, the rectangular seat above a shaped apron and four round legs joined by four stretchers 
39¹⁄₄ in. (101 cm,) high; 27 in. (68.5 cm.) wide; 19¹⁄₂ in. (49.5 cm.) deep, overall 
20¹⁄₂ in. (52 cm.) high; 20 in. (51 cm.) wide; 17¹⁄₄ in. (43.5 cm.) deep, the seat

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF CHINESE HONGMU HORSESHOE-BACK CHAIRS

lots.title_primary_txt: A GROUP OF THREE CHINESE PORCELAIN VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS
lots.description_txt:
Comprising: a celadon baluster vase with craquelure on an ormolu base, a celadon baluster vase modelled with flowering branches and high relief pomegranate handles raised on a carved stained-teak base, and a copper-red glaze baluster vase on a giltwood base; each with pleated cream shades and fitted for electricity 
The green craquelure vase: 15¹⁄₄ in. (38.9 cm.) high, 9 in. (23 cm.) diameter, excluding fitments 
The green pomegranate vase: 13 in. (33 cm.) high; 7¹⁄₂ in. (19 cm.) diameter, excluding fitments 
The red vase: 23¹⁄₂ in. (60 cm.) high; 8¹⁄₂ in. (21.5 in.) diameter, excluding fitments

image.image_alt_text: A GROUP OF THREE CHINESE PORCELAIN VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS

lots.title_primary_txt: A GROUP OF THREE CHINESE PORCELAIN VASES AND COVERS, MOUNTED AS LAMPS
lots.description_txt:
Comprising: a famile rose vase with white ground decorated with birds and flowering lotus and on a circular gilt-metal base, a famille rosevase, the cover with a knob finial between an acanthus-clad harp and baluster body with scrolling floral ground set with shaped cartouches depicting birds and insects amongst flowering branches, and a Ming-style wucai vase with green foliate ground decorated with two male warriors and marked to the underside with apocryphal six-character Ming dynasty reign mark within a double circle; fitted for electricity 
The white-ground vase: 18¹⁄₄ in. (46.5 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 10 in. (25.5 cm.) diameter 
The vase with finial: 19 in. (48 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 10 in. (25.5 cm.) diameter 
The green-ground vase: 15 in. (38 cm.) high, excluding fitments; 9¹⁄₂ in. (24 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A GROUP OF THREE CHINESE PORCELAIN VASES AND COVERS, MOUNTED AS LAMPS

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF FRENCH ORMOLU-MOUNTED MAHOGANY 'JAPONISME' STANDS
lots.description_txt:
Each circular top inset with rouge griotte marble above a frieze with pierced mounts centred by acorns and an intricately carved frieze centred by pierced roundels divided by four legs headed by lion masks, joined by a central shelf and terminating in lion paw feet 
35¹⁄₄ in. (91 cm.) high; 23¹⁄₂ in. (59.5 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF FRENCH ORMOLU-MOUNTED MAHOGANY 'JAPONISME' STANDS

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF CHINESE GLAZED POTTERY HORSES
lots.description_txt:
Each modelled standing on a rectangular base, glazed in brown with touches of green and cream tones 
27 in. (68.5 cm.) high; 27 in. (68.5 cm.) wide; 9 in. (23 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF CHINESE GLAZED POTTERY HORSES

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF CHINESE BLUE AND WHITE PORCELAIN VASES
lots.description_txt:
Each of baluster form and decorated in blue underglaze with dragons chasing a flaming pearl amongst clouds 
19¹⁄₂ in. (49.5 cm.) high; 14¹⁄₂ in. (37 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF CHINESE BLUE AND WHITE PORCELAIN VASES

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF JAPANESE KUTANI-STYLE VASES
lots.description_txt:
Each of slightly tapering form with waisted neck, decorated with red and gilt patchwork ground and centred by a cartouche of a seated maiden and attendants in a landscape framed by dragons, the reverse with a scene of phoenix with a flowering tree, the underside with a nine-character mark and a blue underglaze mark 
21¹⁄₄ in. (54 cm.) high; 9 in. (23 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF JAPANESE KUTANI-STYLE VASES

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF FRENCH 'JAPONISME' ORMOLU-MOUNTED CERAMIC VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS
lots.description_txt:
Each ovi-form 'oeuf' vase with cream craquelure glaze surmounted with lotus finial and fitment above a flower and cross-hatch decoration rim and raised on a circular base with stylised-cloud feet, the underside variously marked 'B700 [?]' 
28¹⁄₂ in. (72.5 cm.) high, including fitments; 6 in. (15.5 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF FRENCH 'JAPONISME' ORMOLU-MOUNTED CERAMIC VASES, MOUNTED AS LAMPS

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF CHINESE FAMILLE ROSE JARDINIERES
lots.description_txt:
Each with circular rim decorated with florals above a red and yellow trellis-ground body decorated with bats and large roundels depicting dragons chasing a flaming pearl 
16¹⁄₄ in. (42.5 cm.) high; 18¹⁄₂ in. (47 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF CHINESE FAMILLE ROSE JARDINIERES

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF REGENCY BRASS-INLAID CALAMANDER, EBONY AND INDIAN ROSEWOOD SIDE CABINETS
lots.title_secondary_txt: IN THE MANNER OF GEORGE OAKLEY, CIRCA 1810
lots.description_txt:
The rectangular top with ebony borders inset with six-pointed stars and brass-banded side edges above a central frieze with decorated 'S'-scroll and anthemion and a glazed door hung with green silk backing and enclosing two adjustable shelves, flanked by conforming star-inset side and on a plinth base 
36 in. (91.5 cm.) high; 23¹⁄₄ in. (60 cm.) wide; 12 in. (30.5 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF REGENCY BRASS-INLAID CALAMANDER, EBONY AND INDIAN ROSEWOOD SIDE CABINETS

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF GEORGE IV BRASS-INLAID ROSEWOOD CARD TABLES
lots.description_txt:
Each with swivel and hinged 'D'-shaped top with a brass-inlaid border decorated with rosettes, enclosing a circular green baize-lining, on square stepped columns with gadrooned collars, a concave-sided quatrefoil platform inset with rosettes flanked by vines and contre-partiefloral roundels, on scrolled feet with brass castors 
30 in. (76 cm.) high; 35 in. (89 cm.) wide; 17¹⁄₄ in. (43.5 cm.) deep, closed 
34¹⁄₄ in. (88.5 cm.) square, open

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF GEORGE IV BRASS-INLAID ROSEWOOD CARD TABLES

lots.title_primary_txt: A WILLIAM IV BRAZILIAN ROSEWOOD AND SPECIMEN HARDSTONE-INLAID TABLE
lots.description_txt:
The rectangular top inset with square specimens of various English hardstones including Blue John, Dukes Red and Purbeck marble, within an up-turned scroll acanthus border above two lyre-form supports centred by rosettes and joined by an arched stretcher, stamped beneath top '017673', raised on four scroll feet  
30¹⁄₄ in. (78 cm.) high; 28 in. (71 cm.) wide; 21 in. (54 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A WILLIAM IV BRAZILIAN ROSEWOOD AND SPECIMEN HARDSTONE-INLAID TABLE

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF CEYLONESE SPECIMEN-WOOD AND BONE-INLAID EBONY HEXAGONAL SIDE TABLES
lots.title_secondary_txt: AFTER THE DESIGN BY THOMAS KING, MID-19TH CENTURY
lots.description_txt:
Each with hexagonal brass and chevron-banded top with leaf-carved edge enclosing centred by a rosette of specimen woods including satinwood, wenge, Indian rosewood, and palmwood divided by diamond-decorated banding, above a moulded frieze enclosing a drawer to one side, on twin leaf-wrapped scrolled supports above rounded rectangular base with leaf-carved borders on down-turned scroll feet  
28¹⁄₂ in. (72.5 cm.) high; 21¹⁄₂ in. 954.5 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF CEYLONESE SPECIMEN-WOOD AND BONE-INLAID EBONY HEXAGONAL SIDE TABLES

lots.title_primary_txt: A WILLIAM IV MAHOGANY WINE COOLER
lots.description_txt:
Of large scale, the oval hinged top with radiating patera centred by a rosette finial, above slightly tapering body with brass escutcheon and enclosing a lead-lined interior, on four baluster feet with castors  
21¹⁄₂ in. (54.5 cm.) high; 29 in. (73.5 cm.) wide; 22 in. (56 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A WILLIAM IV MAHOGANY WINE COOLER

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF CHINESE MOTHER-OF-PEARL, SOAPSTONE, AND HARDSTONE-INLAID BLACK-LACQUER CABINETS
lots.description_txt:
Each with rectangular top above two hinged doors decorated with courtly maidens amongst various landscapes dotted with mountains, pagodas, temples, and gardens and mounted with a central lacquered-brass pin lock and articulated handles, opening to reveal two shelves and flanked by borders of mother-of-pearl inset trellis motifs and painted flowers, the sides decorated with blooming flower stems perched with birds, both with printed label to reverse 'THE ROYAL PAVILION BRIGHTON/ REGENCY EXHIBITION / 1956 /CATALOGUE NUMBER 343', one with old paper labels to the corners of the reverse marked 'A', 'A3', 'A4' the other with labels marked 'B', 'B4', and '...2' 
51¹⁄₂ in. (131 cm.) high; 39 in. (99 cm.) wide; 19 in. (48.5 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF CHINESE MOTHER-OF-PEARL, SOAPSTONE, AND HARDSTONE-INLAID BLACK-LACQUER CABINETS

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF JAPANESE TURQUOISE-GROUND CLOISONNE ENAMEL CHARGERS
lots.description_txt:
Each large circular dish finely decorated with flowering wisteria, peonies, and cherry blossoms against a blue sky with birds and butterflies within a geometric border, the reverse decorated with scrolls against a deeper blue ground 
24 in. (61 cm.) diameter; 3¹⁄₄ in. (9.5 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF JAPANESE TURQUOISE-GROUND CLOISONNE ENAMEL CHARGERS

lots.title_primary_txt: A CHINESE COROMANDEL LACQUER EIGHT-FOLD SCREEN
lots.description_txt:
Decorated to each side with scenes of Chinese figures in a landscape carrying out various pursuits against a dark brown ground, each panel with further individual scenes of landscapes and flowers to the top and base, framed overall with scrolling vines centred by flowers, one side flanked by scenes of dragons to each end 
83 in. (211 cm.) high; 16¹⁄₄ in. (42 cm.) wide, each panel  
130 in. (336 cm.) wide overall, approximately

image.image_alt_text: A CHINESE COROMANDEL LACQUER EIGHT-FOLD SCREEN

lots.title_primary_txt: A CHINESE CLOISONNE-ENAMEL LARGE TRIPOD CENSOR AND COVER, ON STAND
lots.description_txt:
Of large scale, the double-domed cover with lion final and decorated with dragons chasing a flaming pearl, above a bulbous body with scrolling foliate motifs against a turquoise ground and on three beast-headed legs, with apocryphal Qianlong reign mark, on a circular ebonised pine stand 
39¹⁄₂ in. (100 cm.) high; 27¹⁄₄ in. (70.5 cm.) diameter, the censer 
12 in. (30.5 cm.) high; 30 in. (76 cm.), the stand

image.image_alt_text: A CHINESE CLOISONNE-ENAMEL LARGE TRIPOD CENSOR AND COVER, ON STAND

lots.title_primary_txt: A PAIR OF LARGE JAPANESE IMARI VASES AND COVERS, ON STANDS
lots.description_txt:
Each with domed cover decorated with a continuous frieze depicting a dragon chasing its tail and framed with scenes of blooming cherry trees above a baluster-form body profusely decorated with geometric roundels, scrolling foliage, and large alternating scenes of a figure riding an ox in a landscape and phoenix perched in greenery, raised on a carved padouk stand inset with red and white veined marble and carved with floral motifs  
63¹⁄₂ in. (161.5 cm.) high; 24¹⁄₂ in. (62.5 cm.) diameter, the vases 
26¹⁄₄ in. (68 cm.) high; 23¹⁄₂ in. (59.5 cm.) diameter, the stands

image.image_alt_text: A PAIR OF LARGE JAPANESE IMARI VASES AND COVERS, ON STANDS

lots.title_primary_txt: A REGENCY BRASS-INLAID OAK AND INDIAN ROSEWOOD LIBRARY TABLE
lots.description_txt:
The circular rotating top centred by a brown oak roundel outlined and issuing ebony strung radiating panels, encircled by a cut-brass acanthus inlaid outer border above a gadrooned edge, the frieze fitted with eight drawers, on a bowl shaped pedestal carved with basket pattern, on four crouching legs divided by lion masks and terminating in paw feet, on brass castors 
29 in. (75 cm.) high; 52 in. (132 cm.) diameter

image.image_alt_text: A REGENCY BRASS-INLAID OAK AND INDIAN ROSEWOOD LIBRARY TABLE

lots.title_primary_txt: A NORTH ITALIAN GILTWOOD CONSOLE TABLE
lots.description_txt:
The later 'D'-shaped portasanta pink and grey veined marble top above two griffon monopediae and a pair of fluted columnar supports to the back, raised on a faux marble and parcel-gilt concave-fronted base, refreshments to gilding and decoration; the console table reconstructed in its present form probably in the late 19th century  
34 in. (86.5 cm.) high; 39 in. (99 cm.) wide; 18¹⁄₂ in. (47 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A NORTH ITALIAN GILTWOOD CONSOLE TABLE

lots.title_primary_txt: A REGENCY BRASS-MOUNTED BROWN OAK, OAK AND EBONISED OAK LARGE CELLARET
lots.description_txt:
Of large scale, the hinged domed-lid with a lotus finial and scroll handles above a rectangular base with further lion mask handles and berried-laurel wreath mounts to the front and reverse, on ebonised paw feet with later recessed castors, the lion's mask handles and feet probably replaced 
32¹⁄₂ in. (82.5 cm.) high; 42 in. (107 cm.) wide; 28 in. (71 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A REGENCY BRASS-MOUNTED BROWN OAK, OAK AND EBONISED OAK LARGE CELLARET

lots.title_primary_txt: A REGENCY ORMOLU-MOUNTED MAHOGANY AND EBONISED DESK
lots.description_txt:
The rounded rectangular top strung with ebony border above two frieze drawers and two false drawers to the reverse, the short sides mounted with Egyptian-revival winged orbs and the corners with anthemion, on pilaster end supports with volute out-scrolled feet joined by a turned stretcher 
29 in. (74 cm.) high; 44¹⁄₂ in. (113 cm.) wide; 26¹⁄₄ (67 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A REGENCY ORMOLU-MOUNTED MAHOGANY AND EBONISED DESK

lots.title_primary_txt: A LARGE ENGLISH GILTWOOD CONVEX MIRROR
lots.description_txt:
The circular frame with perched eagle cresting flanked by acanthus leaves and suspending from its beak swagged chains and balls, mounted with spheres and five-pointed stars encircling a convex mirror within an ebonised border, above further acanthus and issuing a pair of leaf-clad candle arms with associated cut-glass drip-pans hung with pendants, fitted for electricity 
70¹⁄₂ in. (179 cm.) high; 49¹⁄₂ in. (125.5 cm.) wide; 12 in. (30.5 cm.) deep

image.image_alt_text: A LARGE ENGLISH GILTWOOD CONVEX MIRROR
